"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746477","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-07-05","<p>As I informed the House during my statement of 3 July 2017, and consistent with the commitment set out in the Conservative Party's Northern Ireland manifesto, I intend to bring forward legislation that will provide for the publication of all donations and loans received by Northern Ireland parties on or after the 1 July 2017. This will bring Northern Ireland in line with the rest of the UK with regard to the publication of information relating to political donation and loans.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-07-05T16:37:56.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746477/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746477/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-06-28","Political Parties: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions he has had with the Minister for the Cabinet Office on increasing the public transparency of political donations and donors for parties in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746478","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-07-06","<p>I refer the hon Member to the answer I gave him on 5 July (UIN 1918).</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2017-07-06T11:41:46.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746478/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746478/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746478/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-06-28","Political Parties: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what his policy is on the establishment of a statutory duty on political parties in Northern Ireland to publish details of donations and donors in accordance with practice in the rest of the UK.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","1919"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746479","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-07-03","<p>The Environment Agency recognises that polyurethane foam could cause a risk to health if it catches fire. That is why, in the Bassetlaw constituency, the Environment Agency, county and district councils have set funds aside and are making plans to remove this foam as soon as possible.</p><p> </p><p>The Environment Agency is aware of two further sites where this material has been abandoned.<strong><br> <br> </strong></p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-07-03T12:27:25.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746479/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746479/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746479/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-06-28","Refrigerators: Waste Disposal","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment he has made of the level of potential risk posed by granulated refrigerator foam on abandoned waste sites in the UK; and how many sites are affected by such potential risks.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","1891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746480","Home Office","false","2017-07-03","<p>Asylum accommodation providers are held to the highest standards, including in relation to fire safety. A number of inspections are carried out each year, and where defects are identified we notify the provider and expect these to be fixed within contractual timescales. No issues in relation to fire safety were reported in the years specified under the performance management regime.</p><p>However, to provide the specific information requested would require a manual trawl through all inspection and incident reports, which would breach the disproportionate cost threshold.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","1898 ; 1900 ; 1901","2017-07-03T17:04:56.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746480/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746480/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746480/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-06-28","Compass Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Compass asylum accommodation contract, how many uninhabitable incidents in terms of no operational smoke or fire alarms, under part B.3.1.7 of the Schedule 2 statement of requirements there were in each region covered by that contract in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","1899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746481","Department for Education","false","2017-07-03","<p>The Department has discussed the viability of The Kingsway Academy with the Local Authority (LA) and the Northern Schools Trust (NST) on several occasions since October 2016. The Secretary of State has agreed the school should close by the end of 2017/18 and the Department is working closely with the LA and NST to plan the transition for pupils. The school site will remain in LA ownership and the Department will work with the LA on options for its future use.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","1751 ; 1752 ; 1893","2017-07-03T16:32:52.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746481/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746481/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746481/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-06-28","Kingsway Academy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what discussions she had with Northern Schools Trust on the future use of Kingsway Academy's school site prior to her decision to allow that school to close.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","1892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746482","Department for Education","false","2017-07-03","<p>The Department has discussed the viability of The Kingsway Academy with the Local Authority (LA) and the Northern Schools Trust (NST) on several occasions since October 2016. The Secretary of State has agreed the school should close by the end of 2017/18 and the Department is working closely with the LA and NST to plan the transition for pupils. The school site will remain in LA ownership and the Department will work with the LA on options for its future use.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","1751 ; 1752 ; 1892","2017-07-03T16:32:52.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746482/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746482/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/746482/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-06-28","Kingsway Academy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what steps she will take to ensure that the school site for Kingsway Academy remains in public hands in the event of the closure of that school.","false","Biography information for Ms Angela Eagle","Wallasey","Ms Angela Eagle","1893"
