"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732928","Wales Office","false","2017-07-05","<p>The Wales Office receives its procurement services from the Ministry of Justice and therefore has not put any contracts out to tender.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2017-07-05T11:51:39.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732928/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732928/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732928/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2017-06-27","Wales Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many contracts put out to tender by his Department were awarded to (a) charities and (b) social enterprises in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","1262"
