"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/733095","Department for Education","false","2017-07-05","<p>The Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS) statutory framework sets the standards that all early years providers must meet to ensure that children learn and develop well and are kept healthy and safe. The framework is available at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/early-years-foundation-stage-framework--2" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/early-years-foundation-stage-framework--2</a>.</p><p>The learning and development requirements are informed by the best available evidence on how children learn and reflect the broad range of knowledge and skills that provide the right foundation for good future progress through school and life.</p><p>The 2016 early years foundation stage profile results, which are available at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/early-years-foundation-stage-profile-results-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/statistics/early-years-foundation-stage-profile-results-2015-to-2016</a>, show that 69.3% of children achieved a good level of development (GLD) by age 5, up from 51.7% in 2013.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-07-05T16:27:34.093Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/733095/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/733095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/733095/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-06-27","Pre-school Education: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the OECD's Starting Strong 2017 report, published on 21 June 2017, what steps she is taking to improve early childhood development.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","1395"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/733096","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-07-11","<p>If evacuation is required it will be the responsibility of the landlord to make the necessary arrangements to support residents. Where work is necessary to ensure the fire safety of social housing, we will ensure that lack of financial resources will not prevent it going ahead.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-07-11T09:42:39.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/733096/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/733096/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/733096/answer","Reading West","Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/733096/answer/previousversion/1417","Biography information for Alok Sharma","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-06-27","Fire Prevention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what financial support the Government plans to provide to residents affected by forced evacuations from buildings that fail aluminium composite materials tests.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","1438"
