"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732530","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-04","<p>Public spending per person for the last three years is available for the North West, England and Northern Ireland. This information was published in 2016 in the HM Treasury ‘Country and Regional Analysis’ release. This information is only produced for outturn years, plans information is not produced in this format.</p><p> </p><p>Information on total public sector spending in Ellesmere Port and Neston constituency is not centrally available. The Department for Communities and Local Government collect information on local authority current and capital expenditure, however this forms only part of total public expenditure.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","1054 ; 1055 ; 1056","2017-07-04T14:17:34.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732530/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732530/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732530/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-26","Per Capita Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the total public spending per person has been in (a) England, (b) the North West and (c) Ellesmere Port and Neston constituency in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","1051"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732531","Department for Education","false","2017-07-05","<p>The strongest multi-academy trusts (MATs) have had a transformative effect, turning around the performance of some of the most challenging schools in the country.</p><p>The Department offers a range of support to MATs to support them to be successful and to adopt the practices of the best performing. This can include: advice and guidance, peer-to-peer support, access to professional development activities, and funding.</p><p>Where schools in a trust are underperforming, regional schools commissioners and their teams work with trusts on a case by case basis to determine the best course of action to secure improvement for pupils.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-07-05T16:22:40.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732531/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732531/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732531/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-06-26","Academies: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what her policy is to improve the performance of multi-academy trusts.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","1059"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732532","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-06-29","<p>The Criteria can be found at 1.4.1 and 3.8.2.2 of the Work Capability Assessment Handbook available here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/work-capability-assessment-handbook-for-healthcare-professionals" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/work-capability-assessment-handbook-for-healthcare-professionals</a>.</p><p> </p><p>More detailed advice for healthcare professionals is contained in the Filework Guidelines.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-06-29T15:52:50.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732532/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732532/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732532/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-26","Employment and Support Allowance: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what criteria his Department uses to select employment and support allowance claimants for medical examination.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","1067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732533","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-06-29","<p>The information you have requested can be found here <a href="https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive/contract/1644334/" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive/contract/1644334/</a> in Schedule 2.1, paragraph 46, page 52 of the Health Disability Assessment Service Contract.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-06-29T10:42:51.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732533/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732533/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732533/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-26","Employment and Support Allowance: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the minimum qualification requirements are for people conducting medical examinations on employment and support allowance claimants.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","1068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732534","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-06-29","<p>Just over 0.6% of all face-to-face Work Capability Assessments carried out in the last twelve months generated a complaint to the Centre for Health and Disability Assessments (CHDA).</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-06-29T10:45:33.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732534/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732534/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732534/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-06-26","Employment and Support Allowance: Medical Examinations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many complaints have been made by employment and support allowance claimants after medical examinations.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","1069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732535","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-04","<p>Public spending per person for the last three years is available for the North West, England and Northern Ireland. This information was published in 2016 in the HM Treasury ‘Country and Regional Analysis’ release. This information is only produced for outturn years, plans information is not produced in this format.</p><p> </p><p>Information on total public sector spending in Ellesmere Port and Neston constituency is not centrally available. The Department for Communities and Local Government collect information on local authority current and capital expenditure, however this forms only part of total public expenditure.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","1051 ; 1054 ; 1055","2017-07-04T14:17:34.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732535/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732535/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732535/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-26","Per Capita Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the total public spending per person in (a) England, (b) the North West and (c) Ellesmere Port and Neston constituency in the next three years.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","1056"
