"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732544","HM Treasury","false","2017-07-04","<p>Public spending per person for the last three years is available for the North West, England and Northern Ireland. This information was published in 2016 in the HM Treasury ‘Country and Regional Analysis’ release. This information is only produced for outturn years, plans information is not produced in this format.</p><p> </p><p>Information on total public sector spending in Ellesmere Port and Neston constituency is not centrally available. The Department for Communities and Local Government collect information on local authority current and capital expenditure, however this forms only part of total public expenditure.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","1051 ; 1055 ; 1056","2017-07-04T14:17:34.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732544/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/732544/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-06-26","Per Capita Costs: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the total public spending per person in Northern Ireland has been in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","1054"
